  <h2>Learning Objectives (by Unit)</h2>

  <h3>Unit 1 — Proteins</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Describe/identify general structure and properties of amino acids; classify by side-chain chemistry; explain pH-dependent structure.</li>
    <li>Differentiate primary, secondary, tertiary, and quaternary protein structures and explain stabilizing interactions.</li>
    <li>Apply macromolecule structure/properties to analyze data from common biochemical techniques.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Unit 2 — Enzymes</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Explain thermodynamics of catalyzed vs. uncatalyzed reactions and enzyme–substrate interactions; interpret reaction coordinate diagrams.</li>
    <li>Interpret enzyme-kinetics representations (mechanisms, Michaelis–Menten equation, graphs) and perform calculations with kinetic parameters.</li>
    <li>Differentiate inhibitor types (competitive, noncompetitive, uncompetitive, mixed) and their effects on parameters/representations.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Unit 3 — Nucleic Acids</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Describe/identify general structure and properties of nucleic acids; differentiate DNA vs. RNA; explain stabilizing interactions.</li>
    <li>Explain DNA replication; explain transcription and translation.</li>
    <li>Apply structure/properties to analyze technique-based data.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Unit 4 — Carbohydrates & Lipids</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Describe/identify general structure and properties of carbohydrates; explain common carbohydrate reactions.</li>
    <li>Describe/identify general structure and properties of lipids and lipid membranes.</li>
    <li>Apply structure/properties to analyze technique-based data.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Unit 5 — Metabolism</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Describe/identify ATP/ADP and NAD⁺/NADH and their roles in metabolism.</li>
    <li>Identify key non-reversible enzymes, rate-limiting steps, and regulatory mechanisms in glycolysis and the citric acid cycle.</li>
  </ul>
